.TH G510-DAEMON 1 "2026-03-28" "g510 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
g510-daemon \- Logitech G510/G510s keyboard daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B g510-daemon
[\fB\-c\fR \fIconfig\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-dbus\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-lcd\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B g510-daemon
is a userspace daemon that provides full support for the Logitech G510
and G510s gaming keyboards on Linux.
.PP
It reads G-key events from
.I /dev/input
via evdev, executes macro actions, controls the RGB backlight,
and renders content on the 160\(mu43-pixel LCD GamePanel.
.PP
The daemon auto-detects the keyboard model (G510 vs G510s) using
.BR lsusb (8)
or sysfs. G510s-specific features (headphone/mic mute LEDs, game-mode key)
are enabled automatically.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIfile\fR
Path to the TOML configuration file.
Default:
.I ~/.config/g510/config.toml
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose (DEBUG) logging.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-dbus
Disable the D-Bus interface (useful for testing without a session bus).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-lcd
Disable the LCD GamePanel manager.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/g510/config.toml
User configuration file (created with defaults on first run).
.TP
.I ~/.config/g510/profiles/
Profile JSON files.
.TP
.I /etc/udev/rules.d/99-logitech-g510.rules
udev rules for non-root USB access.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/user/g510-daemon.service
systemd user service unit.
.SH KERNEL REQUIREMENTS
Requires the
.B hid-lg-g15
kernel module, available in mainline Linux since version 5.5.
Check with:
.PP
.RS
.B lsmod | grep hid_lg_g15
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
Start the daemon:
.PP
.RS
.B g510-daemon
.RE
.PP
Start with verbose logging:
.PP
.RS
.B g510-daemon -v
.RE
.PP
Enable as a systemd user service:
.PP
.RS
.B systemctl --user enable --now g510-daemon
.RE
